about.summary: This is primarily meant as an implementation of generalized blockmodeling for valued networks. In addition, measures of similarity or dissimilarity based on structural equivalence and  regular equivalence (REGE algorithms) can be computed and partitioned matrices can be plotted: Žiberna (2007)<doi:10.1016/j.socnet.2006.04.002>, Žiberna (2008)<doi:10.1080/00222500701790207>, Žiberna (2014)<doi:10.1016/j.socnet.2014.04.002>.

name: r-blockmodeling
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.3.4" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-blockmodeling
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/blockmodeling_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/blockmodeling/blockmodeling_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a269c83669dd5294cff0adddab36bc023db6a276a06b74b1fa94b7e407486987

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('fortran') }}  # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_fortran') }}        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-matrix
    - r-doparallel
    - r-dorng
    - r-foreach
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-matrix
    - r-doparallel
    - r-dorng
    - r-foreach

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('blockmodeling')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('blockmodeling')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=blockmodeling
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: "This is primarily meant as an implementation of generalized blockmodeling for valued
    networks. In addition, measures of similarity or dissimilarity based on structural
    equivalence and  regular equivalence (REGE algorithms) can be computed and partitioned
    matrices can be plotted: \u017Diberna (2007)<doi:10.1016/j.socnet.2006.04.002>,
    \u017Diberna (2008)<doi:10.1080/00222500701790207>, \u017Diberna (2014)<doi:10.1016/j.socnet.2014.04.002>."
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
